title: Diary, 1923-1927 [b002] [f003] [V030] [001_074]
author: http://id.loc.gov/authorities/names/no2017006976
description: American journalist and historian Herbert Cooper Thompson worked as a reported for the Associated Press in England and France during World War I and in Mexico during the Mexican Revolution from 1916 to 1918. From 1924 to 1940, he worked as a writer and observer for the American Red Cross, visiting Cuba, Puerto Rico and Europe. Collection comprises diaries, correspondence, literary manuscripts, and photographs by Thompson.|In Washington, D.C. with Red Cross, and on visits to San Francisco and New York
